49// Maps from gof_idx to encoder internal reference frame buffer index. These
50// maps work for 1,2 and 3 temporal layers with GOF length of 1,2 and 4 frames.
51uint8_t kRefBufIdx[4] = {0, 0, 0, 1};
52uint8_t kUpdBufIdx[4] = {0, 0, 1, 0};
53
54// Maximum allowed PID difference for differnet per-layer frame-rate case.
55const int kMaxAllowedPidDiff = 30;
56
57// TODO(ilink): Tune these thresholds further.
58// Selected using ConverenceMotion_1280_720_50.yuv clip.
59// No toggling observed on any link capacity from 100-2000kbps.
60// HD was reached consistently when link capacity was 1500kbps.
61// Set resolutions are a bit more conservative than svc_config.cc sets, e.g.
62// for 300kbps resolution converged to 270p instead of 360p.
63constexpr int kLowVp9QpThreshold = 149;
64constexpr int kHighVp9QpThreshold = 205;
65
66std::pair<size_t, size_t> GetActiveLayers(
67 const VideoBitrateAllocation& allocation) {
68 for (size_t sl_idx = 0; sl_idx < kMaxSpatialLayers; ++sl_idx) {
69 if (allocation.GetSpatialLayerSum(sl_idx) > 0) {
70 size_t last_layer = sl_idx + 1;
71 while (last_layer < kMaxSpatialLayers &&
72 allocation.GetSpatialLayerSum(last_layer) > 0) {
73 ++last_layer;
74 }
75 return std::make_pair(sl_idx, last_layer);
76 }
77 }
78 return {0, 0};
79}

81std::unique_ptr<ScalableVideoController> CreateVp9ScalabilityStructure(
82 const VideoCodec& codec) {
83 int num_spatial_layers = codec.VP9().numberOfSpatialLayers;
84 int num_temporal_layers =
85 std::max(1, int{codec.VP9().numberOfTemporalLayers});
86 if (num_spatial_layers == 1 && num_temporal_layers == 1) {
87 return std::make_unique<ScalableVideoControllerNoLayering>();
88 }
89
90 char name[20];
91 rtc::SimpleStringBuilder ss(name);
92 if (codec.mode == VideoCodecMode::kScreensharing) {
93 // TODO(bugs.webrtc.org/11999): Compose names of the structures when they
94 // are implemented.
95 return nullptr;
96 } else if (codec.VP9().interLayerPred == InterLayerPredMode::kOn ||
97 num_spatial_layers == 1) {
98 ss << "L" << num_spatial_layers << "T" << num_temporal_layers;
99 } else if (codec.VP9().interLayerPred == InterLayerPredMode::kOnKeyPic) {
100 ss << "L" << num_spatial_layers << "T" << num_temporal_layers << "_KEY";
101 } else {
102 RTC_DCHECK_EQ(codec.VP9().interLayerPred, InterLayerPredMode::kOff);
103 ss << "S" << num_spatial_layers << "T" << num_temporal_layers;
104 }
105
106 // Check spatial ratio.
107 if (num_spatial_layers > 1 && codec.spatialLayers[0].targetBitrate > 0) {
108 if (codec.width != codec.spatialLayers[num_spatial_layers - 1].width ||
109 codec.height != codec.spatialLayers[num_spatial_layers - 1].height) {
110 RTC_LOG(LS_WARNING)
111 << "Top layer resolution expected to match overall resolution";
112 return nullptr;
113 }
114 // Check if the ratio is one of the supported.
115 int numerator;
116 int denominator;
117 if (codec.spatialLayers[1].width == 2 * codec.spatialLayers[0].width) {
118 numerator = 1;
119 denominator = 2;
120 // no suffix for 1:2 ratio.
121 } else if (2 * codec.spatialLayers[1].width ==
122 3 * codec.spatialLayers[0].width) {
123 numerator = 2;
124 denominator = 3;
125 ss << "h";
126 } else {
127 RTC_LOG(LS_WARNING) << "Unsupported scalability ratio "
128 << codec.spatialLayers[0].width << ":"
129 << codec.spatialLayers[1].width;
130 return nullptr;
131 }
132 // Validate ratio is consistent for all spatial layer transitions.
133 for (int sid = 1; sid < num_spatial_layers; ++sid) {
134 if (codec.spatialLayers[sid].width * numerator !=
135 codec.spatialLayers[sid - 1].width * denominator ||
136 codec.spatialLayers[sid].height * numerator !=
137 codec.spatialLayers[sid - 1].height * denominator) {
138 RTC_LOG(LS_WARNING) << "Inconsistent scalability ratio " << numerator
139 << ":" << denominator;
140 return nullptr;
141 }
142 }
143 }
144
145 auto scalability_structure_controller = CreateScalabilityStructure(name);
146 if (scalability_structure_controller == nullptr) {
147 RTC_LOG(LS_WARNING) << "Unsupported scalability structure " << name;
148 } else {
149 RTC_LOG(LS_INFO) << "Created scalability structure " << name;
150 }
151 return scalability_structure_controller;
152}

154vpx_svc_ref_frame_config_t Vp9References(
155 rtc::ArrayView<const ScalableVideoController::LayerFrameConfig> layers) {
156 vpx_svc_ref_frame_config_t ref_config = {};
157 for (const ScalableVideoController::LayerFrameConfig& layer_frame : layers) {
158 const auto& buffers = layer_frame.Buffers();
159 RTC_DCHECK_LE(buffers.size(), 3);
160 int sid = layer_frame.SpatialId();
161 if (!buffers.empty()) {
162 ref_config.lst_fb_idx[sid] = buffers[0].id;
163 ref_config.reference_last[sid] = buffers[0].referenced;
164 if (buffers[0].updated) {
165 ref_config.update_buffer_slot[sid] |= (1 << buffers[0].id);
166 }
167 }
168 if (buffers.size() > 1) {
169 ref_config.gld_fb_idx[sid] = buffers[1].id;
170 ref_config.reference_golden[sid] = buffers[1].referenced;
171 if (buffers[1].updated) {
172 ref_config.update_buffer_slot[sid] |= (1 << buffers[1].id);
173 }
174 }
175 if (buffers.size() > 2) {
176 ref_config.alt_fb_idx[sid] = buffers[2].id;
177 ref_config.reference_alt_ref[sid] = buffers[2].referenced;
178 if (buffers[2].updated) {
179 ref_config.update_buffer_slot[sid] |= (1 << buffers[2].id);
180 }
181 }
182 }
183 // TODO(bugs.webrtc.org/11999): Fill ref_config.duration
184 return ref_config;
185}

256int LibvpxVp9Encoder::Release() {
257 int ret_val = WEBRTC_VIDEO_CODEC_OK;
258
259 if (encoder_ != nullptr) {
260 if (inited_) {
261 if (libvpx_->codec_destroy(encoder_)) {
262 ret_val = WEBRTC_VIDEO_CODEC_MEMORY;
263 }
264 }
265 delete encoder_;
266 encoder_ = nullptr;
267 }
268 if (config_ != nullptr) {
269 delete config_;
270 config_ = nullptr;
271 }
272 if (raw_ != nullptr) {
273 libvpx_->img_free(raw_);
274 raw_ = nullptr;
275 }
276 inited_ = false;
277 return ret_val;
278}

286bool LibvpxVp9Encoder::SetSvcRates(
287 const VideoBitrateAllocation& bitrate_allocation) {
288 std::pair<size_t, size_t> current_layers =
289 GetActiveLayers(current_bitrate_allocation_);
290 std::pair<size_t, size_t> new_layers = GetActiveLayers(bitrate_allocation);
291
292 const bool layer_activation_requires_key_frame =
293 inter_layer_pred_ == InterLayerPredMode::kOff ||
294 inter_layer_pred_ == InterLayerPredMode::kOnKeyPic;
295 const bool lower_layers_enabled = new_layers.first < current_layers.first;
296 const bool higher_layers_enabled = new_layers.second > current_layers.second;
297 const bool disabled_layers = new_layers.first > current_layers.first ||
298 new_layers.second < current_layers.second;
299
300 if (lower_layers_enabled ||
301 (higher_layers_enabled && layer_activation_requires_key_frame) ||
302 (disabled_layers && layer_deactivation_requires_key_frame_)) {
303 force_key_frame_ = true;
304 }
305
306 if (current_layers != new_layers) {
307 ss_info_needed_ = true;
308 }
309
310 config_->rc_target_bitrate = bitrate_allocation.get_sum_kbps();
311
312 if (ExplicitlyConfiguredSpatialLayers()) {
313 for (size_t sl_idx = 0; sl_idx < num_spatial_layers_; ++sl_idx) {
314 const bool was_layer_active = (config_->ss_target_bitrate[sl_idx] > 0);
315 config_->ss_target_bitrate[sl_idx] =
316 bitrate_allocation.GetSpatialLayerSum(sl_idx) / 1000;
317
318 for (size_t tl_idx = 0; tl_idx < num_temporal_layers_; ++tl_idx) {
319 config_->layer_target_bitrate[sl_idx * num_temporal_layers_ + tl_idx] =
320 bitrate_allocation.GetTemporalLayerSum(sl_idx, tl_idx) / 1000;
321 }
322
323 if (!was_layer_active) {
324 // Reset frame rate controller if layer is resumed after pause.
325 framerate_controller_[sl_idx].Reset();
326 }
327
328 framerate_controller_[sl_idx].SetTargetRate(
329 codec_.spatialLayers[sl_idx].maxFramerate);
330 }
331 } else {
332 float rate_ratio[VPX_MAX_LAYERS] = {0};
333 float total = 0;
334 for (int i = 0; i < num_spatial_layers_; ++i) {
335 if (svc_params_.scaling_factor_num[i] <= 0 ||
336 svc_params_.scaling_factor_den[i] <= 0) {
337 RTC_LOG(LS_ERROR) << "Scaling factors not specified!";
338 return false;
339 }
340 rate_ratio[i] = static_cast<float>(svc_params_.scaling_factor_num[i]) /
341 svc_params_.scaling_factor_den[i];
342 total += rate_ratio[i];
343 }
344
345 for (int i = 0; i < num_spatial_layers_; ++i) {
346 RTC_CHECK_GT(total, 0);
347 config_->ss_target_bitrate[i] = static_cast<unsigned int>(
348 config_->rc_target_bitrate * rate_ratio[i] / total);
349 if (num_temporal_layers_ == 1) {
350 config_->layer_target_bitrate[i] = config_->ss_target_bitrate[i];
351 } else if (num_temporal_layers_ == 2) {
352 config_->layer_target_bitrate[i * num_temporal_layers_] =
353 config_->ss_target_bitrate[i] * 2 / 3;
354 config_->layer_target_bitrate[i * num_temporal_layers_ + 1] =
355 config_->ss_target_bitrate[i];
356 } else if (num_temporal_layers_ == 3) {
357 config_->layer_target_bitrate[i * num_temporal_layers_] =
358 config_->ss_target_bitrate[i] / 2;
359 config_->layer_target_bitrate[i * num_temporal_layers_ + 1] =
360 config_->layer_target_bitrate[i * num_temporal_layers_] +
361 (config_->ss_target_bitrate[i] / 4);
362 config_->layer_target_bitrate[i * num_temporal_layers_ + 2] =
363 config_->ss_target_bitrate[i];
364 } else {
365 RTC_LOG(LS_ERROR) << "Unsupported number of temporal layers: "
366 << num_temporal_layers_;
367 return false;
368 }
369
370 framerate_controller_[i].SetTargetRate(codec_.maxFramerate);
371 }
372 }
373
374 num_active_spatial_layers_ = 0;
375 first_active_layer_ = 0;
376 bool seen_active_layer = false;
377 bool expect_no_more_active_layers = false;
378 for (int i = 0; i < num_spatial_layers_; ++i) {
379 if (config_->ss_target_bitrate[i] > 0) {
380 RTC_DCHECK(!expect_no_more_active_layers) << "Only middle layer is "
381 "deactivated.";
382 if (!seen_active_layer) {
383 first_active_layer_ = i;
384 }
385 num_active_spatial_layers_ = i + 1;
386 seen_active_layer = true;
387 } else {
388 expect_no_more_active_layers = seen_active_layer;
389 }
390 }
391
392 if (higher_layers_enabled && !force_key_frame_) {
393 // Prohibit drop of all layers for the next frame, so newly enabled
394 // layer would have a valid spatial reference.
395 for (size_t i = 0; i < num_spatial_layers_; ++i) {
396 svc_drop_frame_.framedrop_thresh[i] = 0;
397 }
398 force_all_active_layers_ = true;
399 }
400
401 if (svc_controller_) {
402 VideoBitrateAllocation allocation;
403 for (int sid = 0; sid < num_spatial_layers_; ++sid) {
404 for (int tid = 0; tid < num_temporal_layers_; ++tid) {
405 allocation.SetBitrate(
406 sid, tid,
407 config_->layer_target_bitrate[sid * num_temporal_layers_ + tid] *
408 1000);
409 }
410 }
411 svc_controller_->OnRatesUpdated(allocation);
412 }
413 current_bitrate_allocation_ = bitrate_allocation;
414 config_changed_ = true;
415 return true;
416}

418void LibvpxVp9Encoder::SetRates(const RateControlParameters& parameters) {
419 if (!inited_) {
420 RTC_LOG(LS_WARNING) << "SetRates() calll while uninitialzied.";
421 return;
422 }
423 if (encoder_->err) {
424 RTC_LOG(LS_WARNING) << "Encoder in error state: " << encoder_->err;
425 return;
426 }
427 if (parameters.framerate_fps < 1.0) {
428 RTC_LOG(LS_WARNING) << "Unsupported framerate: "
429 << parameters.framerate_fps;
430 return;
431 }
432
433 codec_.maxFramerate = static_cast<uint32_t>(parameters.framerate_fps + 0.5);
434
435 bool res = SetSvcRates(parameters.bitrate);
436 RTC_DCHECK(res) << "Failed to set new bitrate allocation";
437 config_changed_ = true;
438}

440// TODO(eladalon): s/inst/codec_settings/g.
441int LibvpxVp9Encoder::InitEncode(const VideoCodec* inst,
442 const Settings& settings) {
443 if (inst == nullptr) {
444 return WEBRTC_VIDEO_CODEC_ERR_PARAMETER;
445 }
446 if (inst->maxFramerate < 1) {
447 return WEBRTC_VIDEO_CODEC_ERR_PARAMETER;
448 }
449 // Allow zero to represent an unspecified maxBitRate
450 if (inst->maxBitrate > 0 && inst->startBitrate > inst->maxBitrate) {
451 return WEBRTC_VIDEO_CODEC_ERR_PARAMETER;
452 }
453 if (inst->width < 1 || inst->height < 1) {
454 return WEBRTC_VIDEO_CODEC_ERR_PARAMETER;
455 }
456 if (settings.number_of_cores < 1) {
457 return WEBRTC_VIDEO_CODEC_ERR_PARAMETER;
458 }
459 if (inst->VP9().numberOfTemporalLayers > 3) {
460 return WEBRTC_VIDEO_CODEC_ERR_PARAMETER;
461 }
462 // libvpx probably does not support more than 3 spatial layers.
463 if (inst->VP9().numberOfSpatialLayers > 3) {
464 return WEBRTC_VIDEO_CODEC_ERR_PARAMETER;
465 }
466
467 absl::optional<vpx_img_fmt_t> previous_img_fmt =
468 raw_ ? absl::make_optional<vpx_img_fmt_t>(raw_->fmt) : absl::nullopt;
469
470 int ret_val = Release();
471 if (ret_val < 0) {
472 return ret_val;
473 }
474 if (encoder_ == nullptr) {
475 encoder_ = new vpx_codec_ctx_t;
476 }
477 if (config_ == nullptr) {
478 config_ = new vpx_codec_enc_cfg_t;
479 }
480 timestamp_ = 0;
481 if (&codec_ != inst) {
482 codec_ = *inst;
483 }
484 memset(&svc_params_, 0, sizeof(vpx_svc_extra_cfg_t));
485
486 force_key_frame_ = true;
487 pics_since_key_ = 0;
488
489 num_spatial_layers_ = inst->VP9().numberOfSpatialLayers;
490 RTC_DCHECK_GT(num_spatial_layers_, 0);
491 num_temporal_layers_ = inst->VP9().numberOfTemporalLayers;
492 if (num_temporal_layers_ == 0) {
493 num_temporal_layers_ = 1;
494 }
495
496 if (use_svc_controller_) {
497 svc_controller_ = CreateVp9ScalabilityStructure(*inst);
498 }
499 framerate_controller_ = std::vector<FramerateController>(
500 num_spatial_layers_, FramerateController(codec_.maxFramerate));
501
502 is_svc_ = (num_spatial_layers_ > 1 || num_temporal_layers_ > 1);
503
504 // Populate encoder configuration with default values.
505 if (libvpx_->codec_enc_config_default(vpx_codec_vp9_cx(), config_, 0)) {
506 return WEBRTC_VIDEO_CODEC_ERROR;
507 }
508
509 vpx_img_fmt img_fmt = VPX_IMG_FMT_NONE;
510 unsigned int bits_for_storage = 8;
511 switch (profile_) {
512 case VP9Profile::kProfile0:
513 img_fmt = previous_img_fmt.value_or(VPX_IMG_FMT_I420);
514 bits_for_storage = 8;
515 config_->g_bit_depth = VPX_BITS_8;
516 config_->g_profile = 0;
517 config_->g_input_bit_depth = 8;
518 break;
519 case VP9Profile::kProfile1:
520 // Encoding of profile 1 is not implemented. It would require extended
521 // support for I444, I422, and I440 buffers.
522 RTC_NOTREACHED();
523 break;
524 case VP9Profile::kProfile2:
525 img_fmt = VPX_IMG_FMT_I42016;
526 bits_for_storage = 16;
527 config_->g_bit_depth = VPX_BITS_10;
528 config_->g_profile = 2;
529 config_->g_input_bit_depth = 10;
530 break;
531 }
532
533 // Creating a wrapper to the image - setting image data to nullptr. Actual
534 // pointer will be set in encode. Setting align to 1, as it is meaningless
535 // (actual memory is not allocated).
536 raw_ = libvpx_->img_wrap(nullptr, img_fmt, codec_.width, codec_.height, 1,
537 nullptr);
538 raw_->bit_depth = bits_for_storage;
539
540 config_->g_w = codec_.width;
541 config_->g_h = codec_.height;
542 config_->rc_target_bitrate = inst->startBitrate; // in kbit/s
543 config_->g_error_resilient = is_svc_ ? VPX_ERROR_RESILIENT_DEFAULT : 0;
544 // Setting the time base of the codec.
545 config_->g_timebase.num = 1;
546 config_->g_timebase.den = 90000;
547 config_->g_lag_in_frames = 0; // 0- no frame lagging
548 config_->g_threads = 1;
549 // Rate control settings.
550 config_->rc_dropframe_thresh = inst->VP9().frameDroppingOn ? 30 : 0;
551 config_->rc_end_usage = VPX_CBR;
552 config_->g_pass = VPX_RC_ONE_PASS;
553 config_->rc_min_quantizer =
554 codec_.mode == VideoCodecMode::kScreensharing ? 8 : 2;
555 config_->rc_max_quantizer = 52;
556 config_->rc_undershoot_pct = 50;
557 config_->rc_overshoot_pct = 50;
558 config_->rc_buf_initial_sz = 500;
559 config_->rc_buf_optimal_sz = 600;
560 config_->rc_buf_sz = 1000;
561 // Set the maximum target size of any key-frame.
562 rc_max_intra_target_ = MaxIntraTarget(config_->rc_buf_optimal_sz);
563 // Key-frame interval is enforced manually by this wrapper.
564 config_->kf_mode = VPX_KF_DISABLED;
565 // TODO(webm:1592): work-around for libvpx issue, as it can still
566 // put some key-frames at will even in VPX_KF_DISABLED kf_mode.
567 config_->kf_max_dist = inst->VP9().keyFrameInterval;
568 config_->kf_min_dist = config_->kf_max_dist;
569 if (quality_scaler_experiment_.enabled) {
570 // In that experiment webrtc wide quality scaler is used instead of libvpx
571 // internal scaler.
572 config_->rc_resize_allowed = 0;
573 } else {
574 config_->rc_resize_allowed = inst->VP9().automaticResizeOn ? 1 : 0;
575 }
576 // Determine number of threads based on the image size and #cores.
577 config_->g_threads =
578 NumberOfThreads(config_->g_w, config_->g_h, settings.number_of_cores);
579
580 is_flexible_mode_ = inst->VP9().flexibleMode;
581
582 inter_layer_pred_ = inst->VP9().interLayerPred;
583
584 if (num_spatial_layers_ > 1 &&
585 codec_.mode == VideoCodecMode::kScreensharing && !is_flexible_mode_) {
586 RTC_LOG(LS_ERROR) << "Flexible mode is required for screenshare with "
587 "several spatial layers";
588 return WEBRTC_VIDEO_CODEC_ERR_PARAMETER;
589 }
590
591 // External reference control is required for different frame rate on spatial
592 // layers because libvpx generates rtp incompatible references in this case.
593 external_ref_control_ = external_ref_ctrl_ ||
594 (num_spatial_layers_ > 1 &&
595 codec_.mode == VideoCodecMode::kScreensharing) ||
596 inter_layer_pred_ == InterLayerPredMode::kOn;
597
598 if (num_temporal_layers_ == 1) {
599 gof_.SetGofInfoVP9(kTemporalStructureMode1);
600 config_->temporal_layering_mode = VP9E_TEMPORAL_LAYERING_MODE_NOLAYERING;
601 config_->ts_number_layers = 1;
602 config_->ts_rate_decimator[0] = 1;
603 config_->ts_periodicity = 1;
604 config_->ts_layer_id[0] = 0;
605 } else if (num_temporal_layers_ == 2) {
606 gof_.SetGofInfoVP9(kTemporalStructureMode2);
607 config_->temporal_layering_mode = VP9E_TEMPORAL_LAYERING_MODE_0101;
608 config_->ts_number_layers = 2;
609 config_->ts_rate_decimator[0] = 2;
610 config_->ts_rate_decimator[1] = 1;
611 config_->ts_periodicity = 2;
612 config_->ts_layer_id[0] = 0;
613 config_->ts_layer_id[1] = 1;
614 } else if (num_temporal_layers_ == 3) {
615 gof_.SetGofInfoVP9(kTemporalStructureMode3);
616 config_->temporal_layering_mode = VP9E_TEMPORAL_LAYERING_MODE_0212;
617 config_->ts_number_layers = 3;
618 config_->ts_rate_decimator[0] = 4;
619 config_->ts_rate_decimator[1] = 2;
620 config_->ts_rate_decimator[2] = 1;
621 config_->ts_periodicity = 4;
622 config_->ts_layer_id[0] = 0;
623 config_->ts_layer_id[1] = 2;
624 config_->ts_layer_id[2] = 1;
625 config_->ts_layer_id[3] = 2;
626 } else {
627 return WEBRTC_VIDEO_CODEC_ERR_PARAMETER;
628 }
629
630 if (external_ref_control_) {
631 config_->temporal_layering_mode = VP9E_TEMPORAL_LAYERING_MODE_BYPASS;
632 if (num_temporal_layers_ > 1 && num_spatial_layers_ > 1 &&
633 codec_.mode == VideoCodecMode::kScreensharing) {
634 // External reference control for several temporal layers with different
635 // frame rates on spatial layers is not implemented yet.
636 return WEBRTC_VIDEO_CODEC_ERR_PARAMETER;
637 }
638 }
639 ref_buf_.clear();
640
641 return InitAndSetControlSettings(inst);
642}
643
644int LibvpxVp9Encoder::NumberOfThreads(int width,
645 int height,
646 int number_of_cores) {
647 // Keep the number of encoder threads equal to the possible number of column
648 // tiles, which is (1, 2, 4, 8). See comments below for VP9E_SET_TILE_COLUMNS.
649 if (width * height >= 1280 * 720 && number_of_cores > 4) {
650 return 4;
651 } else if (width * height >= 640 * 360 && number_of_cores > 2) {
652 return 2;
653 } else {
654// Use 2 threads for low res on ARM.
655#if defined(WEBRTC_ARCH_ARM) || defined(WEBRTC_ARCH_ARM64) || \
656 defined(WEBRTC_ANDROID)
657 if (width * height >= 320 * 180 && number_of_cores > 2) {
658 return 2;
659 }
660#endif
661 // 1 thread less than VGA.
662 return 1;
663 }
664}
665
666int LibvpxVp9Encoder::InitAndSetControlSettings(const VideoCodec* inst) {
667 // Set QP-min/max per spatial and temporal layer.
668 int tot_num_layers = num_spatial_layers_ * num_temporal_layers_;
669 for (int i = 0; i < tot_num_layers; ++i) {
670 svc_params_.max_quantizers[i] = config_->rc_max_quantizer;
671 svc_params_.min_quantizers[i] = config_->rc_min_quantizer;
672 }
673 config_->ss_number_layers = num_spatial_layers_;
674 if (svc_controller_) {
675 auto stream_config = svc_controller_->StreamConfig();
676 for (int i = 0; i < stream_config.num_spatial_layers; ++i) {
677 svc_params_.scaling_factor_num[i] = stream_config.scaling_factor_num[i];
678 svc_params_.scaling_factor_den[i] = stream_config.scaling_factor_den[i];
679 }
680 } else if (ExplicitlyConfiguredSpatialLayers()) {
681 for (int i = 0; i < num_spatial_layers_; ++i) {
682 const auto& layer = codec_.spatialLayers[i];
683 RTC_CHECK_GT(layer.width, 0);
684 const int scale_factor = codec_.width / layer.width;
685 RTC_DCHECK_GT(scale_factor, 0);
686
687 // Ensure scaler factor is integer.
688 if (scale_factor * layer.width != codec_.width) {
689 return WEBRTC_VIDEO_CODEC_ERR_PARAMETER;
690 }
691
692 // Ensure scale factor is the same in both dimensions.
693 if (scale_factor * layer.height != codec_.height) {
694 return WEBRTC_VIDEO_CODEC_ERR_PARAMETER;
695 }
696
697 // Ensure scale factor is power of two.
698 const bool is_pow_of_two = (scale_factor & (scale_factor - 1)) == 0;
699 if (!is_pow_of_two) {
700 return WEBRTC_VIDEO_CODEC_ERR_PARAMETER;
701 }
702
703 svc_params_.scaling_factor_num[i] = 1;
704 svc_params_.scaling_factor_den[i] = scale_factor;
705
706 RTC_DCHECK_GT(codec_.spatialLayers[i].maxFramerate, 0);
707 RTC_DCHECK_LE(codec_.spatialLayers[i].maxFramerate, codec_.maxFramerate);
708 if (i > 0) {
709 // Frame rate of high spatial layer is supposed to be equal or higher
710 // than frame rate of low spatial layer.
711 RTC_DCHECK_GE(codec_.spatialLayers[i].maxFramerate,
712 codec_.spatialLayers[i - 1].maxFramerate);
713 }
714 }
715 } else {
716 int scaling_factor_num = 256;
717 for (int i = num_spatial_layers_ - 1; i >= 0; --i) {
718 // 1:2 scaling in each dimension.
719 svc_params_.scaling_factor_num[i] = scaling_factor_num;
720 svc_params_.scaling_factor_den[i] = 256;
721 }
722 }
723
724 SvcRateAllocator init_allocator(codec_);
725 current_bitrate_allocation_ =
726 init_allocator.Allocate(VideoBitrateAllocationParameters(
727 inst->startBitrate * 1000, inst->maxFramerate));
728 if (!SetSvcRates(current_bitrate_allocation_)) {
729 return WEBRTC_VIDEO_CODEC_ERR_PARAMETER;
730 }
731
732 const vpx_codec_err_t rv = libvpx_->codec_enc_init(
733 encoder_, vpx_codec_vp9_cx(), config_,
734 config_->g_bit_depth == VPX_BITS_8 ? 0 : VPX_CODEC_USE_HIGHBITDEPTH);
735 if (rv != VPX_CODEC_OK) {
736 RTC_LOG(LS_ERROR) << "Init error: " << libvpx_->codec_err_to_string(rv);
737 return WEBRTC_VIDEO_CODEC_UNINITIALIZED;
738 }
739
740 UpdatePerformanceFlags();
741 RTC_DCHECK_EQ(performance_flags_by_spatial_index_.size(),
742 static_cast<size_t>(num_spatial_layers_));
743 if (performance_flags_.use_per_layer_speed) {
744 for (int si = 0; si < num_spatial_layers_; ++si) {
745 svc_params_.speed_per_layer[si] =
746 performance_flags_by_spatial_index_[si].base_layer_speed;
747 svc_params_.loopfilter_ctrl[si] =
748 performance_flags_by_spatial_index_[si].deblock_mode;
749 }
750 }
751
752 libvpx_->codec_control(encoder_, VP8E_SET_MAX_INTRA_BITRATE_PCT,
753 rc_max_intra_target_);
754 libvpx_->codec_control(encoder_, VP9E_SET_AQ_MODE,
755 inst->VP9().adaptiveQpMode ? 3 : 0);
756
757 libvpx_->codec_control(encoder_, VP9E_SET_FRAME_PARALLEL_DECODING, 0);
758 libvpx_->codec_control(encoder_, VP9E_SET_SVC_GF_TEMPORAL_REF, 0);
759
760 if (is_svc_) {
761 libvpx_->codec_control(encoder_, VP9E_SET_SVC, 1);
762 libvpx_->codec_control(encoder_, VP9E_SET_SVC_PARAMETERS, &svc_params_);
763 }
764 if (!is_svc_ || !performance_flags_.use_per_layer_speed) {
765 libvpx_->codec_control(
766 encoder_, VP8E_SET_CPUUSED,
767 performance_flags_by_spatial_index_.rbegin()->base_layer_speed);
768 }
769
770 if (num_spatial_layers_ > 1) {
771 switch (inter_layer_pred_) {
772 case InterLayerPredMode::kOn:
773 libvpx_->codec_control(encoder_, VP9E_SET_SVC_INTER_LAYER_PRED, 0);
774 break;
775 case InterLayerPredMode::kOff:
776 libvpx_->codec_control(encoder_, VP9E_SET_SVC_INTER_LAYER_PRED, 1);
777 break;
778 case InterLayerPredMode::kOnKeyPic:
779 libvpx_->codec_control(encoder_, VP9E_SET_SVC_INTER_LAYER_PRED, 2);
780 break;
781 default:
782 RTC_NOTREACHED();
783 }
784
785 memset(&svc_drop_frame_, 0, sizeof(svc_drop_frame_));
786 const bool reverse_constrained_drop_mode =
787 inter_layer_pred_ == InterLayerPredMode::kOn &&
788 codec_.mode == VideoCodecMode::kScreensharing &&
789 num_spatial_layers_ > 1;
790 if (reverse_constrained_drop_mode) {
791 // Screenshare dropping mode: drop a layer only together with all lower
792 // layers. This ensures that drops on lower layers won't reduce frame-rate
793 // for higher layers and reference structure is RTP-compatible.
794 svc_drop_frame_.framedrop_mode = CONSTRAINED_FROM_ABOVE_DROP;
795 svc_drop_frame_.max_consec_drop = 5;
796 for (size_t i = 0; i < num_spatial_layers_; ++i) {
797 svc_drop_frame_.framedrop_thresh[i] = config_->rc_dropframe_thresh;
798 }
799 // No buffering is needed because the highest layer is always present in
800 // all frames in CONSTRAINED_FROM_ABOVE drop mode.
801 layer_buffering_ = false;
802 } else {
803 // Configure encoder to drop entire superframe whenever it needs to drop
804 // a layer. This mode is preferred over per-layer dropping which causes
805 // quality flickering and is not compatible with RTP non-flexible mode.
806 svc_drop_frame_.framedrop_mode =
807 full_superframe_drop_ ? FULL_SUPERFRAME_DROP : CONSTRAINED_LAYER_DROP;
808 // Buffering is needed only for constrained layer drop, as it's not clear
809 // which frame is the last.
810 layer_buffering_ = !full_superframe_drop_;
811 svc_drop_frame_.max_consec_drop = std::numeric_limits<int>::max();
812 for (size_t i = 0; i < num_spatial_layers_; ++i) {
813 svc_drop_frame_.framedrop_thresh[i] = config_->rc_dropframe_thresh;
814 }
815 }
816 libvpx_->codec_control(encoder_, VP9E_SET_SVC_FRAME_DROP_LAYER,
817 &svc_drop_frame_);
818 }
819
820 // Register callback for getting each spatial layer.
821 vpx_codec_priv_output_cx_pkt_cb_pair_t cbp = {
822 LibvpxVp9Encoder::EncoderOutputCodedPacketCallback,
823 reinterpret_cast<void*>(this)};
824 libvpx_->codec_control(encoder_, VP9E_REGISTER_CX_CALLBACK,
825 reinterpret_cast<void*>(&cbp));
826
827 // Control function to set the number of column tiles in encoding a frame, in
828 // log2 unit: e.g., 0 = 1 tile column, 1 = 2 tile columns, 2 = 4 tile columns.
829 // The number tile columns will be capped by the encoder based on image size
830 // (minimum width of tile column is 256 pixels, maximum is 4096).
831 libvpx_->codec_control(encoder_, VP9E_SET_TILE_COLUMNS,
832 static_cast<int>((config_->g_threads >> 1)));
833
834 // Turn on row-based multithreading.
835 libvpx_->codec_control(encoder_, VP9E_SET_ROW_MT, 1);
836
837#if !defined(WEBRTC_ARCH_ARM) && !defined(WEBRTC_ARCH_ARM64) && \
838 !defined(ANDROID)
839 // Do not enable the denoiser on ARM since optimization is pending.
840 // Denoiser is on by default on other platforms.
841 libvpx_->codec_control(encoder_, VP9E_SET_NOISE_SENSITIVITY,
842 inst->VP9().denoisingOn ? 1 : 0);
843#endif
844
845 if (codec_.mode == VideoCodecMode::kScreensharing) {
846 // Adjust internal parameters to screen content.
847 libvpx_->codec_control(encoder_, VP9E_SET_TUNE_CONTENT, 1);
848 }
849 // Enable encoder skip of static/low content blocks.
850 libvpx_->codec_control(encoder_, VP8E_SET_STATIC_THRESHOLD, 1);
851 inited_ = true;
852 config_changed_ = true;
853 return WEBRTC_VIDEO_CODEC_OK;
854}
855
856uint32_t LibvpxVp9Encoder::MaxIntraTarget(uint32_t optimal_buffer_size) {
857 // Set max to the optimal buffer level (normalized by target BR),
858 // and scaled by a scale_par.
859 // Max target size = scale_par * optimal_buffer_size * targetBR[Kbps].
860 // This value is presented in percentage of perFrameBw:
861 // perFrameBw = targetBR[Kbps] * 1000 / framerate.
862 // The target in % is as follows:
863 float scale_par = 0.5;
864 uint32_t target_pct =
865 optimal_buffer_size * scale_par * codec_.maxFramerate / 10;
866 // Don't go below 3 times the per frame bandwidth.
867 const uint32_t min_intra_size = 300;
868 return (target_pct < min_intra_size) ? min_intra_size : target_pct;
869}
870
871int LibvpxVp9Encoder::Encode(const VideoFrame& input_image,
872 const std::vector<VideoFrameType>* frame_types) {
873 if (!inited_) {
874 return WEBRTC_VIDEO_CODEC_UNINITIALIZED;
875 }
876 if (encoded_complete_callback_ == nullptr) {
877 return WEBRTC_VIDEO_CODEC_UNINITIALIZED;
878 }
879 if (num_active_spatial_layers_ == 0) {
880 // All spatial layers are disabled, return without encoding anything.
881 return WEBRTC_VIDEO_CODEC_OK;
882 }
883
884 // We only support one stream at the moment.
885 if (frame_types && !frame_types->empty()) {
886 if ((*frame_types)[0] == VideoFrameType::kVideoFrameKey) {
887 force_key_frame_ = true;
888 }
889 }
890
891 if (pics_since_key_ + 1 ==
892 static_cast<size_t>(codec_.VP9()->keyFrameInterval)) {
893 force_key_frame_ = true;
894 }
895
896 if (svc_controller_) {
897 layer_frames_ = svc_controller_->NextFrameConfig(force_key_frame_);
898 if (layer_frames_.empty()) {
899 return WEBRTC_VIDEO_CODEC_ERROR;
900 }
901 }
902
903 vpx_svc_layer_id_t layer_id = {0};
904 if (!force_key_frame_) {
905 const size_t gof_idx = (pics_since_key_ + 1) % gof_.num_frames_in_gof;
906 layer_id.temporal_layer_id = gof_.temporal_idx[gof_idx];
907
908 if (VideoCodecMode::kScreensharing == codec_.mode) {
909 const uint32_t frame_timestamp_ms =
910 1000 * input_image.timestamp() / kVideoPayloadTypeFrequency;
911
912 // To ensure that several rate-limiters with different limits don't
913 // interfere, they must be queried in order of increasing limit.
914
915 bool use_steady_state_limiter =
916 variable_framerate_experiment_.enabled &&
917 input_image.update_rect().IsEmpty() &&
918 num_steady_state_frames_ >=
919 variable_framerate_experiment_.frames_before_steady_state;
920
921 // Need to check all frame limiters, even if lower layers are disabled,
922 // because variable frame-rate limiter should be checked after the first
923 // layer. It's easier to overwrite active layers after, then check all
924 // cases.
925 for (uint8_t sl_idx = 0; sl_idx < num_active_spatial_layers_; ++sl_idx) {
926 const float layer_fps =
927 framerate_controller_[layer_id.spatial_layer_id].GetTargetRate();
928 // Use steady state rate-limiter at the correct place.
929 if (use_steady_state_limiter &&
930 layer_fps > variable_framerate_experiment_.framerate_limit - 1e-9) {
931 if (variable_framerate_controller_.DropFrame(frame_timestamp_ms)) {
932 layer_id.spatial_layer_id = num_active_spatial_layers_;
933 }
934 // Break always: if rate limiter triggered frame drop, no need to
935 // continue; otherwise, the rate is less than the next limiters.
936 break;
937 }
938 if (framerate_controller_[sl_idx].DropFrame(frame_timestamp_ms)) {
939 ++layer_id.spatial_layer_id;
940 } else {
941 break;
942 }
943 }
944
945 if (use_steady_state_limiter &&
946 layer_id.spatial_layer_id < num_active_spatial_layers_) {
947 variable_framerate_controller_.AddFrame(frame_timestamp_ms);
948 }
949 }
950
951 if (force_all_active_layers_) {
952 layer_id.spatial_layer_id = first_active_layer_;
953 force_all_active_layers_ = false;
954 }
955
956 RTC_DCHECK_LE(layer_id.spatial_layer_id, num_active_spatial_layers_);
957 if (layer_id.spatial_layer_id >= num_active_spatial_layers_) {
958 // Drop entire picture.
959 return WEBRTC_VIDEO_CODEC_OK;
960 }
961 }
962
963 // Need to set temporal layer id on ALL layers, even disabled ones.
964 // Otherwise libvpx might produce frames on a disabled layer:
965 // http://crbug.com/1051476
966 for (int sl_idx = 0; sl_idx < num_spatial_layers_; ++sl_idx) {
967 layer_id.temporal_layer_id_per_spatial[sl_idx] = layer_id.temporal_layer_id;
968 }
969
970 if (layer_id.spatial_layer_id < first_active_layer_) {
971 layer_id.spatial_layer_id = first_active_layer_;
972 }
973
974 if (svc_controller_) {
975 layer_id.spatial_layer_id = layer_frames_.front().SpatialId();
976 layer_id.temporal_layer_id = layer_frames_.front().TemporalId();
977 for (const auto& layer : layer_frames_) {
978 layer_id.temporal_layer_id_per_spatial[layer.SpatialId()] =
979 layer.TemporalId();
980 }
981 }
982
983 if (is_svc_ && performance_flags_.use_per_layer_speed) {
984 // Update speed settings that might depend on temporal index.
985 bool speed_updated = false;
986 for (int sl_idx = 0; sl_idx < num_spatial_layers_; ++sl_idx) {
987 const int target_speed =
988 layer_id.temporal_layer_id_per_spatial[sl_idx] == 0
989 ? performance_flags_by_spatial_index_[sl_idx].base_layer_speed
990 : performance_flags_by_spatial_index_[sl_idx].high_layer_speed;
991 if (svc_params_.speed_per_layer[sl_idx] != target_speed) {
992 svc_params_.speed_per_layer[sl_idx] = target_speed;
993 speed_updated = true;
994 }
995 }
996 if (speed_updated) {
997 libvpx_->codec_control(encoder_, VP9E_SET_SVC_PARAMETERS, &svc_params_);
998 }
999 }
1000
1001 libvpx_->codec_control(encoder_, VP9E_SET_SVC_LAYER_ID, &layer_id);
1002
1003 if (num_spatial_layers_ > 1) {
1004 // Update frame dropping settings as they may change on per-frame basis.
1005 libvpx_->codec_control(encoder_, VP9E_SET_SVC_FRAME_DROP_LAYER,
1006 &svc_drop_frame_);
1007 }
1008
1009 if (config_changed_) {
1010 if (libvpx_->codec_enc_config_set(encoder_, config_)) {
1011 return WEBRTC_VIDEO_CODEC_ERROR;
1012 }
1013
1014 if (!performance_flags_.use_per_layer_speed) {
1015 // Not setting individual speeds per layer, find the highest active
1016 // resolution instead and base the speed on that.
1017 for (int i = num_spatial_layers_ - 1; i >= 0; --i) {
1018 if (config_->ss_target_bitrate[i] > 0) {
1019 int width = (svc_params_.scaling_factor_num[i] * config_->g_w) /
1020 svc_params_.scaling_factor_den[i];
1021 int height = (svc_params_.scaling_factor_num[i] * config_->g_h) /
1022 svc_params_.scaling_factor_den[i];
1023 int speed =
1024 std::prev(performance_flags_.settings_by_resolution.lower_bound(
1025 width * height))
1026 ->second.base_layer_speed;
1027 libvpx_->codec_control(encoder_, VP8E_SET_CPUUSED, speed);
1028 break;
1029 }
1030 }
1031 }
1032 config_changed_ = false;
1033 }
1034
1035 RTC_DCHECK_EQ(input_image.width(), raw_->d_w);
1036 RTC_DCHECK_EQ(input_image.height(), raw_->d_h);
1037
1038 // Set input image for use in the callback.
1039 // This was necessary since you need some information from input_image.
1040 // You can save only the necessary information (such as timestamp) instead of
1041 // doing this.
1042 input_image_ = &input_image;
1043
1044 // In case we need to map the buffer, |mapped_buffer| is used to keep it alive
1045 // through reference counting until after encoding has finished.
1046 rtc::scoped_refptr<const VideoFrameBuffer> mapped_buffer;
1047 const I010BufferInterface* i010_buffer;
1048 rtc::scoped_refptr<const I010BufferInterface> i010_copy;
1049 switch (profile_) {
1050 case VP9Profile::kProfile0: {
1051 mapped_buffer =
1052 PrepareBufferForProfile0(input_image.video_frame_buffer());
1053 if (!mapped_buffer) {
1054 return WEBRTC_VIDEO_CODEC_ERROR;
1055 }
1056 break;
1057 }
1058 case VP9Profile::kProfile1: {
1059 RTC_NOTREACHED();
1060 break;
1061 }
1062 case VP9Profile::kProfile2: {
1063 // We can inject kI010 frames directly for encode. All other formats
1064 // should be converted to it.
1065 switch (input_image.video_frame_buffer()->type()) {
1066 case VideoFrameBuffer::Type::kI010: {
1067 i010_buffer = input_image.video_frame_buffer()->GetI010();
1068 break;
1069 }
1070 default: {
1071 i010_copy =
1072 I010Buffer::Copy(*input_image.video_frame_buffer()->ToI420());
1073 i010_buffer = i010_copy.get();
1074 }
1075 }
1076 raw_->planes[VPX_PLANE_Y] = const_cast<uint8_t*>(
1077 reinterpret_cast<const uint8_t*>(i010_buffer->DataY()));
1078 raw_->planes[VPX_PLANE_U] = const_cast<uint8_t*>(
1079 reinterpret_cast<const uint8_t*>(i010_buffer->DataU()));
1080 raw_->planes[VPX_PLANE_V] = const_cast<uint8_t*>(
1081 reinterpret_cast<const uint8_t*>(i010_buffer->DataV()));
1082 raw_->stride[VPX_PLANE_Y] = i010_buffer->StrideY() * 2;
1083 raw_->stride[VPX_PLANE_U] = i010_buffer->StrideU() * 2;
1084 raw_->stride[VPX_PLANE_V] = i010_buffer->StrideV() * 2;
1085 break;
1086 }
1087 }
1088
1089 vpx_enc_frame_flags_t flags = 0;
1090 if (force_key_frame_) {
1091 flags = VPX_EFLAG_FORCE_KF;
1092 }
1093
1094 if (svc_controller_) {
1095 vpx_svc_ref_frame_config_t ref_config = Vp9References(layer_frames_);
1096 libvpx_->codec_control(encoder_, VP9E_SET_SVC_REF_FRAME_CONFIG,
1097 &ref_config);
1098 } else if (external_ref_control_) {
1099 vpx_svc_ref_frame_config_t ref_config =
1100 SetReferences(force_key_frame_, layer_id.spatial_layer_id);
1101
1102 if (VideoCodecMode::kScreensharing == codec_.mode) {
1103 for (uint8_t sl_idx = 0; sl_idx < num_active_spatial_layers_; ++sl_idx) {
1104 ref_config.duration[sl_idx] = static_cast<int64_t>(
1105 90000 / (std::min(static_cast<float>(codec_.maxFramerate),
1106 framerate_controller_[sl_idx].GetTargetRate())));
1107 }
1108 }
1109
1110 libvpx_->codec_control(encoder_, VP9E_SET_SVC_REF_FRAME_CONFIG,
1111 &ref_config);
1112 }
1113
1114 first_frame_in_picture_ = true;
1115
1116 // TODO(ssilkin): Frame duration should be specified per spatial layer
1117 // since their frame rate can be different. For now calculate frame duration
1118 // based on target frame rate of the highest spatial layer, which frame rate
1119 // is supposed to be equal or higher than frame rate of low spatial layers.
1120 // Also, timestamp should represent actual time passed since previous frame
1121 // (not 'expected' time). Then rate controller can drain buffer more
1122 // accurately.
1123 RTC_DCHECK_GE(framerate_controller_.size(), num_active_spatial_layers_);
1124 float target_framerate_fps =
1125 (codec_.mode == VideoCodecMode::kScreensharing)
1126 ? std::min(static_cast<float>(codec_.maxFramerate),
1127 framerate_controller_[num_active_spatial_layers_ - 1]
1128 .GetTargetRate())
1129 : codec_.maxFramerate;
1130 uint32_t duration = static_cast<uint32_t>(90000 / target_framerate_fps);
1131 const vpx_codec_err_t rv = libvpx_->codec_encode(
1132 encoder_, raw_, timestamp_, duration, flags, VPX_DL_REALTIME);
1133 if (rv != VPX_CODEC_OK) {
1134 RTC_LOG(LS_ERROR) << "Encoding error: " << libvpx_->codec_err_to_string(rv)
1135 << "\n"
1136 "Details: "
1137 << libvpx_->codec_error(encoder_) << "\n"
1138 << libvpx_->codec_error_detail(encoder_);
1139 return WEBRTC_VIDEO_CODEC_ERROR;
1140 }
1141 timestamp_ += duration;
1142
1143 if (layer_buffering_) {
1144 const bool end_of_picture = true;
1145 DeliverBufferedFrame(end_of_picture);
1146 }
1147
1148 return WEBRTC_VIDEO_CODEC_OK;
1149}
1150
1151bool LibvpxVp9Encoder::PopulateCodecSpecific(CodecSpecificInfo* codec_specific,
1152 absl::optional<int>* spatial_idx,
1153 const vpx_codec_cx_pkt& pkt,
1154 uint32_t timestamp) {
1155 RTC_CHECK(codec_specific != nullptr);
1156 codec_specific->codecType = kVideoCodecVP9;
1157 CodecSpecificInfoVP9* vp9_info = &(codec_specific->codecSpecific.VP9);
1158
1159 vp9_info->first_frame_in_picture = first_frame_in_picture_;
1160 vp9_info->flexible_mode = is_flexible_mode_;
1161
1162 if (pkt.data.frame.flags & VPX_FRAME_IS_KEY) {
1163 pics_since_key_ = 0;
1164 } else if (first_frame_in_picture_) {
1165 ++pics_since_key_;
1166 }
1167
1168 vpx_svc_layer_id_t layer_id = {0};
1169 libvpx_->codec_control(encoder_, VP9E_GET_SVC_LAYER_ID, &layer_id);
1170
1171 // Can't have keyframe with non-zero temporal layer.
1172 RTC_DCHECK(pics_since_key_ != 0 || layer_id.temporal_layer_id == 0);
1173
1174 RTC_CHECK_GT(num_temporal_layers_, 0);
1175 RTC_CHECK_GT(num_active_spatial_layers_, 0);
1176 if (num_temporal_layers_ == 1) {
1177 RTC_CHECK_EQ(layer_id.temporal_layer_id, 0);
1178 vp9_info->temporal_idx = kNoTemporalIdx;
1179 } else {
1180 vp9_info->temporal_idx = layer_id.temporal_layer_id;
1181 }
1182 if (num_active_spatial_layers_ == 1) {
1183 RTC_CHECK_EQ(layer_id.spatial_layer_id, 0);
1184 *spatial_idx = absl::nullopt;
1185 } else {
1186 *spatial_idx = layer_id.spatial_layer_id;
1187 }
1188
1189 // TODO(asapersson): this info has to be obtained from the encoder.
1190 vp9_info->temporal_up_switch = false;
1191
1192 const bool is_key_pic = (pics_since_key_ == 0);
1193 const bool is_inter_layer_pred_allowed =
1194 (inter_layer_pred_ == InterLayerPredMode::kOn ||
1195 (inter_layer_pred_ == InterLayerPredMode::kOnKeyPic && is_key_pic));
1196
1197 // Always set inter_layer_predicted to true on high layer frame if inter-layer
1198 // prediction (ILP) is allowed even if encoder didn't actually use it.
1199 // Setting inter_layer_predicted to false would allow receiver to decode high
1200 // layer frame without decoding low layer frame. If that would happen (e.g.
1201 // if low layer frame is lost) then receiver won't be able to decode next high
1202 // layer frame which uses ILP.
1203 vp9_info->inter_layer_predicted =
1204 first_frame_in_picture_ ? false : is_inter_layer_pred_allowed;
1205
1206 // Mark all low spatial layer frames as references (not just frames of
1207 // active low spatial layers) if inter-layer prediction is enabled since
1208 // these frames are indirect references of high spatial layer, which can
1209 // later be enabled without key frame.
1210 vp9_info->non_ref_for_inter_layer_pred =
1211 !is_inter_layer_pred_allowed ||
1212 layer_id.spatial_layer_id + 1 == num_spatial_layers_;
1213
1214 // Always populate this, so that the packetizer can properly set the marker
1215 // bit.
1216 vp9_info->num_spatial_layers = num_active_spatial_layers_;
1217 vp9_info->first_active_layer = first_active_layer_;
1218
1219 vp9_info->num_ref_pics = 0;
1220 FillReferenceIndices(pkt, pics_since_key_, vp9_info->inter_layer_predicted,
1221 vp9_info);
1222 if (vp9_info->flexible_mode) {
1223 vp9_info->gof_idx = kNoGofIdx;
1224 } else {
1225 vp9_info->gof_idx =
1226 static_cast<uint8_t>(pics_since_key_ % gof_.num_frames_in_gof);
1227 vp9_info->temporal_up_switch = gof_.temporal_up_switch[vp9_info->gof_idx];
1228 RTC_DCHECK(vp9_info->num_ref_pics == gof_.num_ref_pics[vp9_info->gof_idx] ||
1229 vp9_info->num_ref_pics == 0);
1230 }
1231
1232 vp9_info->inter_pic_predicted = (!is_key_pic && vp9_info->num_ref_pics > 0);
1233
1234 // Write SS on key frame of independently coded spatial layers and on base
1235 // temporal/spatial layer frame if number of layers changed without issuing
1236 // of key picture (inter-layer prediction is enabled).
1237 const bool is_key_frame = is_key_pic && !vp9_info->inter_layer_predicted;
1238 if (is_key_frame || (ss_info_needed_ && layer_id.temporal_layer_id == 0 &&
1239 layer_id.spatial_layer_id == first_active_layer_)) {
1240 vp9_info->ss_data_available = true;
1241 vp9_info->spatial_layer_resolution_present = true;
1242 // Signal disabled layers.
1243 for (size_t i = 0; i < first_active_layer_; ++i) {
1244 vp9_info->width[i] = 0;
1245 vp9_info->height[i] = 0;
1246 }
1247 for (size_t i = first_active_layer_; i < num_active_spatial_layers_; ++i) {
1248 vp9_info->width[i] = codec_.width * svc_params_.scaling_factor_num[i] /
1249 svc_params_.scaling_factor_den[i];
1250 vp9_info->height[i] = codec_.height * svc_params_.scaling_factor_num[i] /
1251 svc_params_.scaling_factor_den[i];
1252 }
1253 if (vp9_info->flexible_mode) {
1254 vp9_info->gof.num_frames_in_gof = 0;
1255 } else {
1256 vp9_info->gof.CopyGofInfoVP9(gof_);
1257 }
1258
1259 ss_info_needed_ = false;
1260 } else {
1261 vp9_info->ss_data_available = false;
1262 }
1263
1264 first_frame_in_picture_ = false;
1265
1266 // Populate codec-agnostic section in the codec specific structure.
1267 if (svc_controller_) {
1268 auto it = absl::c_find_if(
1269 layer_frames_,
1270 [&](const ScalableVideoController::LayerFrameConfig& config) {
1271 return config.SpatialId() == layer_id.spatial_layer_id;
1272 });
1273 if (it == layer_frames_.end()) {
1274 RTC_LOG(LS_ERROR) << "Encoder produced a frame for layer S"
1275 << layer_id.spatial_layer_id << "T"
1276 << layer_id.temporal_layer_id
1277 << " that wasn't requested.";
1278 return false;
1279 }
1280 codec_specific->generic_frame_info = svc_controller_->OnEncodeDone(*it);
1281 if (is_key_frame) {
1282 codec_specific->template_structure =
1283 svc_controller_->DependencyStructure();
1284 auto& resolutions = codec_specific->template_structure->resolutions;
1285 resolutions.resize(num_spatial_layers_);
1286 for (int sid = 0; sid < num_spatial_layers_; ++sid) {
1287 resolutions[sid] = RenderResolution(
1288 /*width=*/codec_.width * svc_params_.scaling_factor_num[sid] /
1289 svc_params_.scaling_factor_den[sid],
1290 /*height=*/codec_.height * svc_params_.scaling_factor_num[sid] /
1291 svc_params_.scaling_factor_den[sid]);
1292 }
1293 }
1294 }
1295 return true;
1296}
1297
1298void LibvpxVp9Encoder::FillReferenceIndices(const vpx_codec_cx_pkt& pkt,
1299 const size_t pic_num,
1300 const bool inter_layer_predicted,
1301 CodecSpecificInfoVP9* vp9_info) {
1302 vpx_svc_layer_id_t layer_id = {0};
1303 libvpx_->codec_control(encoder_, VP9E_GET_SVC_LAYER_ID, &layer_id);
1304
1305 const bool is_key_frame =
1306 (pkt.data.frame.flags & VPX_FRAME_IS_KEY) ? true : false;
1307
1308 std::vector<RefFrameBuffer> ref_buf_list;
1309
1310 if (is_svc_) {
1311 vpx_svc_ref_frame_config_t enc_layer_conf = {{0}};
1312 libvpx_->codec_control(encoder_, VP9E_GET_SVC_REF_FRAME_CONFIG,
1313 &enc_layer_conf);
1314 int ref_buf_flags = 0;
1315
1316 if (enc_layer_conf.reference_last[layer_id.spatial_layer_id]) {
1317 const size_t fb_idx =
1318 enc_layer_conf.lst_fb_idx[layer_id.spatial_layer_id];
1319 RTC_DCHECK(ref_buf_.find(fb_idx) != ref_buf_.end());
1320 if (std::find(ref_buf_list.begin(), ref_buf_list.end(),
1321 ref_buf_.at(fb_idx)) == ref_buf_list.end()) {
1322 ref_buf_list.push_back(ref_buf_.at(fb_idx));
1323 ref_buf_flags |= 1 << fb_idx;
1324 }
1325 }
1326
1327 if (enc_layer_conf.reference_alt_ref[layer_id.spatial_layer_id]) {
1328 const size_t fb_idx =
1329 enc_layer_conf.alt_fb_idx[layer_id.spatial_layer_id];
1330 RTC_DCHECK(ref_buf_.find(fb_idx) != ref_buf_.end());
1331 if (std::find(ref_buf_list.begin(), ref_buf_list.end(),
1332 ref_buf_.at(fb_idx)) == ref_buf_list.end()) {
1333 ref_buf_list.push_back(ref_buf_.at(fb_idx));
1334 ref_buf_flags |= 1 << fb_idx;
1335 }
1336 }
1337
1338 if (enc_layer_conf.reference_golden[layer_id.spatial_layer_id]) {
1339 const size_t fb_idx =
1340 enc_layer_conf.gld_fb_idx[layer_id.spatial_layer_id];
1341 RTC_DCHECK(ref_buf_.find(fb_idx) != ref_buf_.end());
1342 if (std::find(ref_buf_list.begin(), ref_buf_list.end(),
1343 ref_buf_.at(fb_idx)) == ref_buf_list.end()) {
1344 ref_buf_list.push_back(ref_buf_.at(fb_idx));
1345 ref_buf_flags |= 1 << fb_idx;
1346 }
1347 }
1348
1349 RTC_LOG(LS_VERBOSE) << "Frame " << pic_num << " sl "
1350 << layer_id.spatial_layer_id << " tl "
1351 << layer_id.temporal_layer_id << " refered buffers "
1352 << (ref_buf_flags & (1 << 0) ? 1 : 0)
1353 << (ref_buf_flags & (1 << 1) ? 1 : 0)
1354 << (ref_buf_flags & (1 << 2) ? 1 : 0)
1355 << (ref_buf_flags & (1 << 3) ? 1 : 0)
1356 << (ref_buf_flags & (1 << 4) ? 1 : 0)
1357 << (ref_buf_flags & (1 << 5) ? 1 : 0)
1358 << (ref_buf_flags & (1 << 6) ? 1 : 0)
1359 << (ref_buf_flags & (1 << 7) ? 1 : 0);
1360
1361 } else if (!is_key_frame) {
1362 RTC_DCHECK_EQ(num_spatial_layers_, 1);
1363 RTC_DCHECK_EQ(num_temporal_layers_, 1);
1364 // In non-SVC mode encoder doesn't provide reference list. Assume each frame
1365 // refers previous one, which is stored in buffer 0.
1366 ref_buf_list.push_back(ref_buf_.at(0));
1367 }
1368
1369 size_t max_ref_temporal_layer_id = 0;
1370
1371 std::vector<size_t> ref_pid_list;
1372
1373 vp9_info->num_ref_pics = 0;
1374 for (const RefFrameBuffer& ref_buf : ref_buf_list) {
1375 RTC_DCHECK_LE(ref_buf.pic_num, pic_num);
1376 if (ref_buf.pic_num < pic_num) {
1377 if (inter_layer_pred_ != InterLayerPredMode::kOn) {
1378 // RTP spec limits temporal prediction to the same spatial layer.
1379 // It is safe to ignore this requirement if inter-layer prediction is
1380 // enabled for all frames when all base frames are relayed to receiver.
1381 RTC_DCHECK_EQ(ref_buf.spatial_layer_id, layer_id.spatial_layer_id);
1382 } else {
1383 RTC_DCHECK_LE(ref_buf.spatial_layer_id, layer_id.spatial_layer_id);
1384 }
1385 RTC_DCHECK_LE(ref_buf.temporal_layer_id, layer_id.temporal_layer_id);
1386
1387 // Encoder may reference several spatial layers on the same previous
1388 // frame in case if some spatial layers are skipped on the current frame.
1389 // We shouldn't put duplicate references as it may break some old
1390 // clients and isn't RTP compatible.
1391 if (std::find(ref_pid_list.begin(), ref_pid_list.end(),
1392 ref_buf.pic_num) != ref_pid_list.end()) {
1393 continue;
1394 }
1395 ref_pid_list.push_back(ref_buf.pic_num);
1396
1397 const size_t p_diff = pic_num - ref_buf.pic_num;
1398 RTC_DCHECK_LE(p_diff, 127UL);
1399
1400 vp9_info->p_diff[vp9_info->num_ref_pics] = static_cast<uint8_t>(p_diff);
1401 ++vp9_info->num_ref_pics;
1402
1403 max_ref_temporal_layer_id =
1404 std::max(max_ref_temporal_layer_id, ref_buf.temporal_layer_id);
1405 } else {
1406 RTC_DCHECK(inter_layer_predicted);
1407 // RTP spec only allows to use previous spatial layer for inter-layer
1408 // prediction.
1409 RTC_DCHECK_EQ(ref_buf.spatial_layer_id + 1, layer_id.spatial_layer_id);
1410 }
1411 }
1412
1413 vp9_info->temporal_up_switch =
1414 (max_ref_temporal_layer_id <
1415 static_cast<size_t>(layer_id.temporal_layer_id));
1416}
1417
1418void LibvpxVp9Encoder::UpdateReferenceBuffers(const vpx_codec_cx_pkt& pkt,
1419 const size_t pic_num) {
1420 vpx_svc_layer_id_t layer_id = {0};
1421 libvpx_->codec_control(encoder_, VP9E_GET_SVC_LAYER_ID, &layer_id);
1422
1423 RefFrameBuffer frame_buf(pic_num, layer_id.spatial_layer_id,
1424 layer_id.temporal_layer_id);
1425
1426 if (is_svc_) {
1427 vpx_svc_ref_frame_config_t enc_layer_conf = {{0}};
1428 libvpx_->codec_control(encoder_, VP9E_GET_SVC_REF_FRAME_CONFIG,
1429 &enc_layer_conf);
1430 const int update_buffer_slot =
1431 enc_layer_conf.update_buffer_slot[layer_id.spatial_layer_id];
1432
1433 for (size_t i = 0; i < kNumVp9Buffers; ++i) {
1434 if (update_buffer_slot & (1 << i)) {
1435 ref_buf_[i] = frame_buf;
1436 }
1437 }
1438
1439 RTC_LOG(LS_VERBOSE) << "Frame " << pic_num << " sl "
1440 << layer_id.spatial_layer_id << " tl "
1441 << layer_id.temporal_layer_id << " updated buffers "
1442 << (update_buffer_slot & (1 << 0) ? 1 : 0)
1443 << (update_buffer_slot & (1 << 1) ? 1 : 0)
1444 << (update_buffer_slot & (1 << 2) ? 1 : 0)
1445 << (update_buffer_slot & (1 << 3) ? 1 : 0)
1446 << (update_buffer_slot & (1 << 4) ? 1 : 0)
1447 << (update_buffer_slot & (1 << 5) ? 1 : 0)
1448 << (update_buffer_slot & (1 << 6) ? 1 : 0)
1449 << (update_buffer_slot & (1 << 7) ? 1 : 0);
1450 } else {
1451 RTC_DCHECK_EQ(num_spatial_layers_, 1);
1452 RTC_DCHECK_EQ(num_temporal_layers_, 1);
1453 // In non-svc mode encoder doesn't provide reference list. Assume each frame
1454 // is reference and stored in buffer 0.
1455 ref_buf_[0] = frame_buf;
1456 }
1457}
1458
1459vpx_svc_ref_frame_config_t LibvpxVp9Encoder::SetReferences(
1460 bool is_key_pic,
1461 size_t first_active_spatial_layer_id) {
1462 // kRefBufIdx, kUpdBufIdx need to be updated to support longer GOFs.
1463 RTC_DCHECK_LE(gof_.num_frames_in_gof, 4);
1464
1465 vpx_svc_ref_frame_config_t ref_config;
1466 memset(&ref_config, 0, sizeof(ref_config));
1467
1468 const size_t num_temporal_refs = std::max(1, num_temporal_layers_ - 1);
1469 const bool is_inter_layer_pred_allowed =
1470 inter_layer_pred_ == InterLayerPredMode::kOn ||
1471 (inter_layer_pred_ == InterLayerPredMode::kOnKeyPic && is_key_pic);
1472 absl::optional<int> last_updated_buf_idx;
1473
1474 // Put temporal reference to LAST and spatial reference to GOLDEN. Update
1475 // frame buffer (i.e. store encoded frame) if current frame is a temporal
1476 // reference (i.e. it belongs to a low temporal layer) or it is a spatial
1477 // reference. In later case, always store spatial reference in the last
1478 // reference frame buffer.
1479 // For the case of 3 temporal and 3 spatial layers we need 6 frame buffers
1480 // for temporal references plus 1 buffer for spatial reference. 7 buffers
1481 // in total.
1482
1483 for (size_t sl_idx = first_active_spatial_layer_id;
1484 sl_idx < num_active_spatial_layers_; ++sl_idx) {
1485 const size_t curr_pic_num = is_key_pic ? 0 : pics_since_key_ + 1;
1486 const size_t gof_idx = curr_pic_num % gof_.num_frames_in_gof;
1487
1488 if (!is_key_pic) {
1489 // Set up temporal reference.
1490 const int buf_idx = sl_idx * num_temporal_refs + kRefBufIdx[gof_idx];
1491
1492 // Last reference frame buffer is reserved for spatial reference. It is
1493 // not supposed to be used for temporal prediction.
1494 RTC_DCHECK_LT(buf_idx, kNumVp9Buffers - 1);
1495
1496 const int pid_diff = curr_pic_num - ref_buf_[buf_idx].pic_num;
1497 // Incorrect spatial layer may be in the buffer due to a key-frame.
1498 const bool same_spatial_layer =
1499 ref_buf_[buf_idx].spatial_layer_id == sl_idx;
1500 bool correct_pid = false;
1501 if (is_flexible_mode_) {
1502 correct_pid = pid_diff > 0 && pid_diff < kMaxAllowedPidDiff;
1503 } else {
1504 // Below code assumes single temporal referecence.
1505 RTC_DCHECK_EQ(gof_.num_ref_pics[gof_idx], 1);
1506 correct_pid = pid_diff == gof_.pid_diff[gof_idx][0];
1507 }
1508
1509 if (same_spatial_layer && correct_pid) {
1510 ref_config.lst_fb_idx[sl_idx] = buf_idx;
1511 ref_config.reference_last[sl_idx] = 1;
1512 } else {
1513 // This reference doesn't match with one specified by GOF. This can
1514 // only happen if spatial layer is enabled dynamically without key
1515 // frame. Spatial prediction is supposed to be enabled in this case.
1516 RTC_DCHECK(is_inter_layer_pred_allowed &&
1517 sl_idx > first_active_spatial_layer_id);
1518 }
1519 }
1520
1521 if (is_inter_layer_pred_allowed && sl_idx > first_active_spatial_layer_id) {
1522 // Set up spatial reference.
1523 RTC_DCHECK(last_updated_buf_idx);
1524 ref_config.gld_fb_idx[sl_idx] = *last_updated_buf_idx;
1525 ref_config.reference_golden[sl_idx] = 1;
1526 } else {
1527 RTC_DCHECK(ref_config.reference_last[sl_idx] != 0 ||
1528 sl_idx == first_active_spatial_layer_id ||
1529 inter_layer_pred_ == InterLayerPredMode::kOff);
1530 }
1531
1532 last_updated_buf_idx.reset();
1533
1534 if (gof_.temporal_idx[gof_idx] < num_temporal_layers_ - 1 ||
1535 num_temporal_layers_ == 1) {
1536 last_updated_buf_idx = sl_idx * num_temporal_refs + kUpdBufIdx[gof_idx];
1537
1538 // Ensure last frame buffer is not used for temporal prediction (it is
1539 // reserved for spatial reference).
1540 RTC_DCHECK_LT(*last_updated_buf_idx, kNumVp9Buffers - 1);
1541 } else if (is_inter_layer_pred_allowed) {
1542 last_updated_buf_idx = kNumVp9Buffers - 1;
1543 }
1544
1545 if (last_updated_buf_idx) {
1546 ref_config.update_buffer_slot[sl_idx] = 1 << *last_updated_buf_idx;
1547 }
1548 }
1549
1550 return ref_config;
1551}
1552
1553void LibvpxVp9Encoder::GetEncodedLayerFrame(const vpx_codec_cx_pkt* pkt) {
1554 RTC_DCHECK_EQ(pkt->kind, VPX_CODEC_CX_FRAME_PKT);
1555
1556 if (pkt->data.frame.sz == 0) {
1557 // Ignore dropped frame.
1558 return;
1559 }
1560
1561 vpx_svc_layer_id_t layer_id = {0};
1562 libvpx_->codec_control(encoder_, VP9E_GET_SVC_LAYER_ID, &layer_id);
1563
1564 if (layer_buffering_) {
1565 // Deliver buffered low spatial layer frame.
1566 const bool end_of_picture = false;
1567 DeliverBufferedFrame(end_of_picture);
1568 }
1569
1570 // TODO(nisse): Introduce some buffer cache or buffer pool, to reduce
1571 // allocations and/or copy operations.
1572 encoded_image_.SetEncodedData(EncodedImageBuffer::Create(
1573 static_cast<const uint8_t*>(pkt->data.frame.buf), pkt->data.frame.sz));
1574
1575 const bool is_key_frame =
1576 (pkt->data.frame.flags & VPX_FRAME_IS_KEY) ? true : false;
1577 // Ensure encoder issued key frame on request.
1578 RTC_DCHECK(is_key_frame || !force_key_frame_);
1579
1580 // Check if encoded frame is a key frame.
1581 encoded_image_._frameType = VideoFrameType::kVideoFrameDelta;
1582 if (is_key_frame) {
1583 encoded_image_._frameType = VideoFrameType::kVideoFrameKey;
1584 force_key_frame_ = false;
1585 }
1586
1587 codec_specific_ = {};
1588 absl::optional<int> spatial_index;
1589 if (!PopulateCodecSpecific(&codec_specific_, &spatial_index, *pkt,
1590 input_image_->timestamp())) {
1591 // Drop the frame.
1592 encoded_image_.set_size(0);
1593 return;
1594 }
1595 encoded_image_.SetSpatialIndex(spatial_index);
1596
1597 UpdateReferenceBuffers(*pkt, pics_since_key_);
1598
1599 TRACE_COUNTER1("webrtc", "EncodedFrameSize", encoded_image_.size());
1600 encoded_image_.SetTimestamp(input_image_->timestamp());
1601 encoded_image_._encodedHeight =
1602 pkt->data.frame.height[layer_id.spatial_layer_id];
1603 encoded_image_._encodedWidth =
1604 pkt->data.frame.width[layer_id.spatial_layer_id];
1605 int qp = -1;
1606 libvpx_->codec_control(encoder_, VP8E_GET_LAST_QUANTIZER, &qp);
1607 encoded_image_.qp_ = qp;
1608
1609 if (!layer_buffering_) {
1610 const bool end_of_picture = encoded_image_.SpatialIndex().value_or(0) + 1 ==
1611 num_active_spatial_layers_;
1612 DeliverBufferedFrame(end_of_picture);
1613 }
1614}
1615
1616void LibvpxVp9Encoder::DeliverBufferedFrame(bool end_of_picture) {
1617 if (encoded_image_.size() > 0) {
1618 if (num_spatial_layers_ > 1) {
1619 // Restore frame dropping settings, as dropping may be temporary forbidden
1620 // due to dynamically enabled layers.
1621 for (size_t i = 0; i < num_spatial_layers_; ++i) {
1622 svc_drop_frame_.framedrop_thresh[i] = config_->rc_dropframe_thresh;
1623 }
1624 }
1625
1626 codec_specific_.end_of_picture = end_of_picture;
1627
1628 encoded_complete_callback_->OnEncodedImage(encoded_image_,
1629 &codec_specific_);
1630
1631 if (codec_.mode == VideoCodecMode::kScreensharing) {
1632 const uint8_t spatial_idx = encoded_image_.SpatialIndex().value_or(0);
1633 const uint32_t frame_timestamp_ms =
1634 1000 * encoded_image_.Timestamp() / kVideoPayloadTypeFrequency;
1635 framerate_controller_[spatial_idx].AddFrame(frame_timestamp_ms);
1636
1637 const size_t steady_state_size = SteadyStateSize(
1638 spatial_idx, codec_specific_.codecSpecific.VP9.temporal_idx);
1639
1640 // Only frames on spatial layers, which may be limited in a steady state
1641 // are considered for steady state detection.
1642 if (framerate_controller_[spatial_idx].GetTargetRate() >
1643 variable_framerate_experiment_.framerate_limit + 1e-9) {
1644 if (encoded_image_.qp_ <=
1645 variable_framerate_experiment_.steady_state_qp &&
1646 encoded_image_.size() <= steady_state_size) {
1647 ++num_steady_state_frames_;
1648 } else {
1649 num_steady_state_frames_ = 0;
1650 }
1651 }
1652 }
1653 encoded_image_.set_size(0);
1654 }
1655}

1658 EncodedImageCallback* callback) {
1659 encoded_complete_callback_ = callback;
1660 return WEBRTC_VIDEO_CODEC_OK;

1663VideoEncoder::EncoderInfo LibvpxVp9Encoder::GetEncoderInfo() const {
1664 EncoderInfo info;
1665 info.supports_native_handle = false;
1666 info.implementation_name = "libvpx";
1667 if (quality_scaler_experiment_.enabled && inited_ &&
1668 codec_.VP9().automaticResizeOn) {
1669 info.scaling_settings = VideoEncoder::ScalingSettings(
1670 quality_scaler_experiment_.low_qp, quality_scaler_experiment_.high_qp);
1671 } else {
1672 info.scaling_settings = VideoEncoder::ScalingSettings::kOff;
1673 }
1674 info.has_trusted_rate_controller = trusted_rate_controller_;
1675 info.is_hardware_accelerated = false;
1676 info.has_internal_source = false;
1677 if (inited_) {
1678 // Find the max configured fps of any active spatial layer.
1679 float max_fps = 0.0;
1680 for (size_t si = 0; si < num_spatial_layers_; ++si) {
1681 if (codec_.spatialLayers[si].active &&
1682 codec_.spatialLayers[si].maxFramerate > max_fps) {
1683 max_fps = codec_.spatialLayers[si].maxFramerate;
1684 }
1685 }
1686
1687 for (size_t si = 0; si < num_spatial_layers_; ++si) {
1688 info.fps_allocation[si].clear();
1689 if (!codec_.spatialLayers[si].active) {
1690 continue;
1691 }
1692
1693 // This spatial layer may already use a fraction of the total frame rate.
1694 const float sl_fps_fraction =
1695 codec_.spatialLayers[si].maxFramerate / max_fps;
1696 for (size_t ti = 0; ti < num_temporal_layers_; ++ti) {
1697 const uint32_t decimator =
1698 num_temporal_layers_ <= 1 ? 1 : config_->ts_rate_decimator[ti];
1699 RTC_DCHECK_GT(decimator, 0);
1700 info.fps_allocation[si].push_back(
1701 rtc::saturated_cast<uint8_t>(EncoderInfo::kMaxFramerateFraction *
1702 (sl_fps_fraction / decimator)));
1703 }
1704 }
1705 if (profile_ == VP9Profile::kProfile0) {
1706 info.preferred_pixel_formats = {VideoFrameBuffer::Type::kI420,
1707 VideoFrameBuffer::Type::kNV12};
1708 }
1709 }
1710 if (!encoder_info_override_.resolution_bitrate_limits().empty()) {
1711 info.resolution_bitrate_limits =
1712 encoder_info_override_.resolution_bitrate_limits();
1713 }
1714 return info;
1715}

1717size_t LibvpxVp9Encoder::SteadyStateSize(int sid, int tid) {
1718 const size_t bitrate_bps = current_bitrate_allocation_.GetBitrate(
1719 sid, tid == kNoTemporalIdx ? 0 : tid);
1720 const float fps = (codec_.mode == VideoCodecMode::kScreensharing)
1721 ? std::min(static_cast<float>(codec_.maxFramerate),
1722 framerate_controller_[sid].GetTargetRate())
1723 : codec_.maxFramerate;
1724 return static_cast<size_t>(
1725 bitrate_bps / (8 * fps) *
1726 (100 -
1727 variable_framerate_experiment_.steady_state_undershoot_percentage) /
1728 100 +
1729 0.5);
1730}

1773void LibvpxVp9Encoder::UpdatePerformanceFlags() {
1774 const auto find_speed = [&](int min_pixel_count) {
1775 RTC_DCHECK(!performance_flags_.settings_by_resolution.empty());
1776 auto it =
1777 performance_flags_.settings_by_resolution.upper_bound(min_pixel_count);
1778 return std::prev(it)->second;
1779 };
1780
1781 performance_flags_by_spatial_index_.clear();
1782 if (is_svc_) {
1783 for (int si = 0; si < num_spatial_layers_; ++si) {
1784 performance_flags_by_spatial_index_.push_back(find_speed(
1785 codec_.spatialLayers[si].width * codec_.spatialLayers[si].height));
1786 }
1787 } else {
1788 performance_flags_by_spatial_index_.push_back(
1789 find_speed(codec_.width * codec_.height));
1790 }
1791}

1793// static
1794LibvpxVp9Encoder::PerformanceFlags
1795LibvpxVp9Encoder::ParsePerformanceFlagsFromTrials(
1796 const WebRtcKeyValueConfig& trials) {
1797 struct Params : public PerformanceFlags::ParameterSet {
1798 int min_pixel_count = 0;
1799 };
1800
1801 FieldTrialStructList<Params> trials_list(
1802 {FieldTrialStructMember("min_pixel_count",
1803 [](Params* p) { return &p->min_pixel_count; }),
1804 FieldTrialStructMember("high_layer_speed",
1805 [](Params* p) { return &p->high_layer_speed; }),
1806 FieldTrialStructMember("base_layer_speed",
1807 [](Params* p) { return &p->base_layer_speed; }),
1808 FieldTrialStructMember("deblock_mode",
1809 [](Params* p) { return &p->deblock_mode; })},
1810 {});
1811
1812 FieldTrialFlag per_layer_speed("use_per_layer_speed");
1813
1814 ParseFieldTrial({&trials_list, &per_layer_speed},
1815 trials.Lookup("WebRTC-VP9-PerformanceFlags"));
1816
1817 PerformanceFlags flags;
1818 flags.use_per_layer_speed = per_layer_speed.Get();
1819
1820 constexpr int kMinSpeed = 1;
1821 constexpr int kMaxSpeed = 9;
1822 for (auto& f : trials_list.Get()) {
1823 if (f.base_layer_speed < kMinSpeed || f.base_layer_speed > kMaxSpeed ||
1824 f.high_layer_speed < kMinSpeed || f.high_layer_speed > kMaxSpeed ||
1825 f.deblock_mode < 0 || f.deblock_mode > 2) {
1826 RTC_LOG(LS_WARNING) << "Ignoring invalid performance flags: "
1827 << "min_pixel_count = " << f.min_pixel_count
1828 << ", high_layer_speed = " << f.high_layer_speed
1829 << ", base_layer_speed = " << f.base_layer_speed
1830 << ", deblock_mode = " << f.deblock_mode;
1831 continue;
1832 }
1833 flags.settings_by_resolution[f.min_pixel_count] = f;
1834 }
1835
1836 if (flags.settings_by_resolution.empty()) {
1837 return GetDefaultPerformanceFlags();
1838 }
1839
1840 return flags;
1841}

1843// static
1844LibvpxVp9Encoder::PerformanceFlags
1845LibvpxVp9Encoder::GetDefaultPerformanceFlags() {
1846 PerformanceFlags flags;
1847 flags.use_per_layer_speed = false;
1848#if defined(WEBRTC_ARCH_ARM) || defined(WEBRTC_ARCH_ARM64) || defined(ANDROID)
1849 // Speed 8 on all layers for all resolutions.
1850 flags.settings_by_resolution[0] = {8, 8, 0};
1851#else
1852 // For smaller resolutions, use lower speed setting (get some coding gain at
1853 // the cost of increased encoding complexity).
1854 flags.settings_by_resolution[0] = {5, 5, 0};
1855
1856 // Use speed 7 for QCIF and above.
1857 flags.settings_by_resolution[352 * 288] = {7, 7, 0};
1858#endif
1859 return flags;
1860}

1862void LibvpxVp9Encoder::MaybeRewrapRawWithFormat(const vpx_img_fmt fmt) {
1863 if (!raw_) {
1864 raw_ = libvpx_->img_wrap(nullptr, fmt, codec_.width, codec_.height, 1,
1865 nullptr);
1866 } else if (raw_->fmt != fmt) {
1867 RTC_LOG(INFO) << "Switching VP9 encoder pixel format to "
1868 << (fmt == VPX_IMG_FMT_NV12 ? "NV12" : "I420");
1869 libvpx_->img_free(raw_);
1870 raw_ = libvpx_->img_wrap(nullptr, fmt, codec_.width, codec_.height, 1,
1871 nullptr);
1872 }
1873 // else no-op since the image is already in the right format.
1874}

1876rtc::scoped_refptr<VideoFrameBuffer> LibvpxVp9Encoder::PrepareBufferForProfile0(
1877 rtc::scoped_refptr<VideoFrameBuffer> buffer) {
1878 absl::InlinedVector<VideoFrameBuffer::Type, kMaxPreferredPixelFormats>
1879 supported_formats = {VideoFrameBuffer::Type::kI420,
1880 VideoFrameBuffer::Type::kNV12};
1881
1882 rtc::scoped_refptr<VideoFrameBuffer> mapped_buffer;
1883 if (buffer->type() != VideoFrameBuffer::Type::kNative) {
1884 // |buffer| is already mapped.
1885 mapped_buffer = buffer;
1886 } else {
1887 // Attempt to map to one of the supported formats.
1888 mapped_buffer = buffer->GetMappedFrameBuffer(supported_formats);
1889 }
1890 if (!mapped_buffer ||
1891 (absl::c_find(supported_formats, mapped_buffer->type()) ==
1892 supported_formats.end() &&
1893 mapped_buffer->type() != VideoFrameBuffer::Type::kI420A)) {
1894 // Unknown pixel format or unable to map, convert to I420 and prepare that
1895 // buffer instead to ensure Scale() is safe to use.
1896 auto converted_buffer = buffer->ToI420();
1897 if (!converted_buffer) {
1898 RTC_LOG(LS_ERROR) << "Failed to convert "
1899 << VideoFrameBufferTypeToString(buffer->type())
1900 << " image to I420. Can't encode frame.";
1901 return {};
1902 }
1903 // The buffer should now be a mapped I420 or I420A format, but some buffer
1904 // implementations incorrectly return the wrong buffer format, such as
1905 // kNative. As a workaround to this, we perform ToI420() a second time.
1906 // TODO(https://crbug.com/webrtc/12602): When Android buffers have a correct
1907 // ToI420() implementaion, remove his workaround.
1908 if (converted_buffer->type() != VideoFrameBuffer::Type::kI420 &&
1909 converted_buffer->type() != VideoFrameBuffer::Type::kI420A) {
1910 converted_buffer = converted_buffer->ToI420();
1911 RTC_CHECK(converted_buffer->type() == VideoFrameBuffer::Type::kI420 ||
1912 converted_buffer->type() == VideoFrameBuffer::Type::kI420A);
1913 }
1914 // Because |buffer| had to be converted, use |converted_buffer| instead.
1915 buffer = mapped_buffer = converted_buffer;
1916 }
1917
1918 // Prepare |raw_| from |mapped_buffer|.
1919 switch (mapped_buffer->type()) {
1920 case VideoFrameBuffer::Type::kI420:
1921 case VideoFrameBuffer::Type::kI420A: {
1922 MaybeRewrapRawWithFormat(VPX_IMG_FMT_I420);
1923 const I420BufferInterface* i420_buffer = mapped_buffer->GetI420();
1924 RTC_DCHECK(i420_buffer);
1925 raw_->planes[VPX_PLANE_Y] = const_cast<uint8_t*>(i420_buffer->DataY());
1926 raw_->planes[VPX_PLANE_U] = const_cast<uint8_t*>(i420_buffer->DataU());
1927 raw_->planes[VPX_PLANE_V] = const_cast<uint8_t*>(i420_buffer->DataV());
1928 raw_->stride[VPX_PLANE_Y] = i420_buffer->StrideY();
1929 raw_->stride[VPX_PLANE_U] = i420_buffer->StrideU();
1930 raw_->stride[VPX_PLANE_V] = i420_buffer->StrideV();
1931 break;
1932 }
1933 case VideoFrameBuffer::Type::kNV12: {
1934 MaybeRewrapRawWithFormat(VPX_IMG_FMT_NV12);
1935 const NV12BufferInterface* nv12_buffer = mapped_buffer->GetNV12();
1936 RTC_DCHECK(nv12_buffer);
1937 raw_->planes[VPX_PLANE_Y] = const_cast<uint8_t*>(nv12_buffer->DataY());
1938 raw_->planes[VPX_PLANE_U] = const_cast<uint8_t*>(nv12_buffer->DataUV());
1939 raw_->planes[VPX_PLANE_V] = raw_->planes[VPX_PLANE_U] + 1;
1940 raw_->stride[VPX_PLANE_Y] = nv12_buffer->StrideY();
1941 raw_->stride[VPX_PLANE_U] = nv12_buffer->StrideUV();
1942 raw_->stride[VPX_PLANE_V] = nv12_buffer->StrideUV();
1943 break;
1944 }
1945 default:
1946 RTC_NOTREACHED();
1947 }
1948 return mapped_buffer;
1949}
